column11: The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up!  TIP: Sensors -  If the ship goes dark, don't panic. Just fix the Sensors Subsystem.
There are no more life-signs remaining on the ship. You strip it of useful materials.
Your jump leads to a remarkable binary star system. The view is beautiful, but there is nothing else around.
The ship refuses to fight, but you still detect life signatures. Apparently this was a prisoner transport. The single survivor offers to join your crew in exchange for their freedom.

There is only one other ship at this beacon, and it is showing heavy damage. You receive a message on your console: Greetings traveler. We were crippled by a band of pirates and are now forced to sell our remaining valuable equipment to acquire the necessary supplies to get home.
column12: System: drones, battery, hacking, Weapon: MISSILES 3, ION 4, LASER HULL 2, Drone: REPAIR, COMBAT BEAM 2, ANTI DRONE, Augment: ION ARMOR, SHIELD RECHARGE, REPAIR ARM,

column11: Searching the remains you find that the cargo was military-grade Drone Schematics! You bring them aboard to install on your ship.
With the crew dead, you are able to take the fuel out of storage. You also take all the scrap you can manage.
Their ship goes silent and you are relieved to know that you are still one step ahead of the fleet.
There are no more life-signs remaining on the ship. You strip it of useful materials.
There are no more life-signs remaining on the ship. You strip it of useful materials.
This sector has been largely abandoned since a series of battles decimated the local population. An unusual alien race is reportedly scavenging in the area. You'd best be on guard.
You arrive at an empty space station, no doubt abandoned due to the Lanius threat. Life signatures are detected at the ship depot and you spot a few crude signs stating Everything Must Go!
column12: System: drones, battery, clonebay, Weapon: MISSILES HULL, BEAM 2, LASER CHARGEGUN 2, Crew: Human, Mantis, Human, Drone: REPAIR, COMBAT FIRE, DEFENSE 1,

column11: You use your ship's Cloaking to try to prevent the defense system from getting a lock. However before you are able to safely disable the system your cloaking gives out and you are forced to destroy the satellite. No one was harmed but they don't seem happy with your solution.
Thank you. Here, have this extra scrap as payment.
You finish off your assailant with the help of the Anti-Ship Battery but the fight rages on in the distance. You'd best leave before you get dragged into it again.

You come across a human civilian ship preparing to leave the sector. They message you, We're getting out of here! There was some cult rambling about the spreading of the disease, Humanitis. They forcefully boarded our ship and tried to open all of our airlocks, shouting, Be purged! Is nowhere safe anymore?
With help from the computer, you are able to keep a comfortable distance between you and the Lanius ship, and you are able to gather resources from the debris field without conflict.

A trading depot is set up near the beacon. A surprising number of military ships guard the station. You pick up an advertisement on a wide band channel, Ship parts, repairs, refueling, souvenirs - we got it all. Check out the only store not afraid of scavengers this side of Omacron 6.
column12: Drone: COMBAT BEAM, DEFENSE 1, COMBAT 1, System: battery, clonebay, mind,

column11: You find a weapon system on their ship. With no crew to stop you, you can install it on your own.

An image of some weak and hungry humans comes onto your screen. Those metal bastards think they can just absorb half of our engines and leave us here to die? I hope you understand the need to take your ship by force.
You thank them for the information and prepare to jump.
The computer matches the rotation and speed of the target ship, and you take the opportunity to gather what residual scrap you can without awakening the Lanius crew. You get an excellent haul!
Holy crap! A weapon is just floating in space!
Welcome to a new sector! Get to the exit beacon and jump to the next sector before the pursuing Rebels catch you!
You find a weapon system on their ship. With no crew to stop you, you can install it on your own.
With the crew dead, you are able to take the fuel out of storage. You also take all the scrap you can manage.
The station is a storage site for various resources. You salvage everything possible.
Now that their ship has been emptied of hostiles, you search it. Eventually you find a prisoner who offers to join your crew.
Most of the debris is hardly even usable as scrap. However, you eventually find an intact weapon that can be mounted on your ship.
Searching the remains you find that the cargo was military-grade Drone Schematics! You bring them aboard to install on your ship.
Without active sensors you have no other option but to look out of the view-ports in apprehension. It's eerily quiet.
You cycle through wide-band comm channels as soon as you arrive. Nothing but static.

You use your ion weaponry to disable the gun long enough for their repair crews to fix it. They message you, I've never seen a weapon like that before! Thanks for your help. Please accept this reward.
Thank you for your business.
The asteroid field proved more dangerous than expected. Some asteroids managed to get through your ship's defenses.
There are no more life-signs remaining on the ship. You strip it of useful materials.
You have arrived in Engi space. The fall of the Federation has brought tough times for these robotic lifeforms, but they're usually willing to help.
Slightly shocked at your question, their leader quickly responds, Declined offer with apologetic gratitude. Topic of discussion private matter, no concern of Federation.
They thank you for the assistance and when you tell them of your mission, one of the Engi asks if he can assist your crew. You welcome him aboard.
This system appears quite peaceful. You're not sure how long it'll last between the combined threats of the Rebels and Mantis.
You're able to safely refuel and get clear before the station explodes.
You find a pirate ship, damaged and abandoned. You salvage what you can and move on.
An Engi ship hails: Engine upgrade necessary for travel home. Sale of equipment necessary for engine upgrade.
column12: Drone: ANTI DRONE, DEFENSE 1, BATTLE, Weapon: BOMB 1, LASER BURST 2 A, BEAM LONG,

column11: A message arrives: Your scrap, ours. Our weapons for you. You're about to raise the shields when you realize it's just an Engi trader looking for a trade.
column12: System: battery, clonebay, hacking, Crew: Engi, Engi, Engi,

column11: Your crew-member is able to remotely fix the glitch in the defense AI, allowing the repair crew to close in and finish the job. The station gives you its thanks along with a reward.
You transfer down some missile warheads and the Engi rig them to blow before setting a distress signal to attract the fleet's attention.
The Engi can do remarkable things with just a pile of scrap. The Engi hive at this beacon are selling equipment for just that.
column12: System: clonebay, mind, hacking, Augment: AUTO COOLDOWN, REPAIR ARM, BATTERY BOOSTER,

column11: With all of the would-be pirates dead, you think it best not to return to the settlement... You prepare to jump.

Your crew calmly lines up for the Zoltans to take their readings. After a short time, the process is done. They contact you, Thank you for your participation in our study. Please accept these small cakes made from stiff dough as well as some scrap.
Good choice, son. We've both come out of this richer.
The Zoltan patrol their borders but let you pass when you ID as Federation. Let's hope they won't be so courteous to the Rebels.
Thank you for rescuing us! They held us hostage to ambush unsuspecting passersby. Please, take this.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
As you're salvaging the Mantis wreck the Zoltan security patrol returns with three other ships. You quickly salvage what you can and set off before they can stop you for questioning.
The Zoltan are fascinated by other species, and have set up something of an alien knick-knack shop here. Why not take a look?

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You feel naked without functioning sensors. You half expect a Rebel ship to appear from behind a cloud at any moment, but none come.
There are no more life-signs remaining on the ship. You strip it of useful materials.
You can't see anything through the thick gases surrounding your ship. Without knowing what is out there, all you can do is wait for your FTL to charge.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You don't have time to hail the Zoltan ship that was waiting at this beacon before it jumps away. They are a careful race.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You let their team on board and after a short time they finish their work.
You're far from Federation home space here in Zoltan territory, and it's not clear whether the authorities will have any goodwill remaining. Still, you have to push forward.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
There are some mineral-rich asteroids here that the Zoltan have left idle, but you've none of the necessary equipment to mine them.
As you wait for the FTL drive to charge, you half expect to be ambushed at any moment. However, no attack comes...
You cycle through wide-band comm channels as soon as you arrive. Nothing but static.
Most of the debris is hardly even usable as scrap. However, you eventually find an intact weapon that can be mounted on your ship.
There are no more life-signs remaining on the ship. You strip it of useful materials.

As you approach, a kaleidoscope of colors fills the viewscreen and one of your crew begins to age rapidly in reverse, eventually disappearing into nothingness. Let's hope they've transcended physical existence, and not just been forced out of it.
The Zoltan are fascinated by other species, and have set up something of an alien knick-knack shop here. Why not take a look?

column11: A few Federation-friendly planets still exist in this sector, but they are constantly under attack by pirate raids. This is a dangerous sector, so be careful.

column11: Take this bit of scrap as a down-payment. We'll use your jump signatures to follow you. You're really helping us out here. Added a quest marker to your map!
